<h2>Lesson Summary:</h2>
<p>
<!-- Introduction to course schedule and standards, followed by an overview of 
the general issues and best practices for securing information systems. Most of the 
class will be dedicated to setting up the VMs and admin info. -->
In this lesson, we explore design and security systems of the Microsoft Windows OS family.
Using Windows 7 we will introduce concepts such as 
account management, the Windows CMD Line, SAM Database and permissions management. 
Students will leave this lesson with an 
understanding of how to harden Windows systems.
</p>

<h2>Lesson Objectives:</h2>
<ul>
<li>Identify basic Windows structure</li>
<li>Explain Windows security issues and implications of a closed source design</li>
<li>Secure key services</li>
<li>Implement logging</li>
<li>Implement application whitelisting</li>
<li>Understand file permissions structure and how to implement the concept of least privilege</li>
<li>Effectively operate in a Windows CMD Line environment</li>
</ul>

